<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Containing Blocks - top, bottom, and right padding depend on rtl direction when ancestor is inline-level and positioned absolutely</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#containing-block-details" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="If the ancestor is inline-level, postioned absolute, and direction is rtl, the top/right of the containing block determines the top/right padding edges of the first box generated by the ancestor." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #s1
            {
                position: absolute;
                direction: rtl;
                display: inline;
                background: red;
                border: solid 3px black;
                width: 100px;
                height: 100px;
            }
            #s2
            {
                position: absolute;
                padding-bottom: 10px;
                padding-right: 10px;
                background: green;
                width: 90px;
                height: 90px;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if there is no red visible on the page.</p>
        <span id="s1">
            <span id="s2">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>
        </span>
    </body>
</html>